main event: A military radar operator and pilot observed an unidentified object moving at high speeds and greater altitude than their aircraft in 1952.
interesting points: The object was observed both on radar and visually by the pilot and radar operator.
The object's speed and altitude exceeded that of the observing aircraft.
The object's maneuvers were not consistent with known aircraft.
The report concluded that the object was unknown with no explanation.
No physical evidence or photographs of the object were obtained.
